@page "/components/checkbox"

<PageTitle>Checkbox - ShadcnBlazor</PageTitle>
<HeadContent>
    <meta name="description" content="ShadcnBlazor Checkbox - Selection input for true/false or multiple option selections." />
</HeadContent>
@using System.Reflection
@using ShadcnBlazor.Docs.Pages.Components.Checkbox.Examples
@using ShadcnBlazor.Docs.Services

<ComponentDocPage Metadata="@Metadata"
                 InstallCommand="@InstallCommand"
                 ApiDoc="@ApiDocumentation.Checkbox">
    <DocsSection Title="Usage" Id="usage">
        <p>The Checkbox component is a standalone control that should be paired with a <code>Label</code> component for proper labeling. Use the <code>Id</code> parameter on the checkbox and the <code>For</code> parameter on the label to associate them. Bind <code>Value</code> for two-way state, or use <code>ValueChanged</code> for one-way updates.</p>
        <ComponentPreview CodeFiles="@(new[] { Snippets.Components_Checkbox_Examples_CheckboxBasicExample })">
            <CheckboxBasicExample />
        </ComponentPreview>
    </DocsSection>

    <DocsSection Title="Examples" Id="examples">
        <DocsSubSection Title="With Label" Id="with-label">
            <p>Pair the checkbox with a <code>Label</code> component using matching <code>Id</code> and <code>For</code> attributes. Wrap them together in a flex container for proper layout.</p>
            <ComponentPreview CodeFiles="@(new[] { Snippets.Components_Checkbox_Examples_CheckboxLabelExample })">
                <CheckboxLabelExample />
            </ComponentPreview>
        </DocsSubSection>
        <DocsSubSection Title="With Description" Id="with-description">
            <p>Add a description below the label by nesting the label and description text in a flex column. Align the checkbox to the start of the group using <code>items-start</code>.</p>
            <ComponentPreview CodeFiles="@(new[] { Snippets.Components_Checkbox_Examples_CheckboxAlignmentWithDescriptionExample })">
                <CheckboxAlignmentWithDescriptionExample />
            </ComponentPreview>
        </DocsSubSection>
        <DocsSubSection Title="In a Field" Id="in-field">
            <p>Use the checkbox within a <code>Field</code> component for structured form layout with labels and descriptions. The <code>FieldDescription</code> provides helper text below the label.</p>
            <ComponentPreview CodeFiles="@(new[] { Snippets.Components_Checkbox_Examples_CheckboxInFieldExample })">
                <CheckboxInFieldExample />
            </ComponentPreview>
        </DocsSubSection>
        <DocsSubSection Title="Grouping" Id="grouping">
            <p>Use multiple checkboxes in a flex column to create a checkbox group. Bind each via <code>Value</code> and <code>ValueChanged</code> to a shared collection (e.g. <code>HashSet&lt;string&gt;</code>) to track selections.</p>
            <ComponentPreview CodeFiles="@(new[] { Snippets.Components_Checkbox_Examples_CheckboxGroupingExample })">
                <CheckboxGroupingExample />
            </ComponentPreview>
        </DocsSubSection>
        <DocsSubSection Title="Disabled" Id="disabled">
            <p>Use the <code>Disabled</code> parameter to prevent interaction. The checkbox is dimmed and cannot be toggled.</p>
            <ComponentPreview CodeFiles="@(new[] { Snippets.Components_Checkbox_Examples_CheckboxDisabledExample })">
                <CheckboxDisabledExample />
            </ComponentPreview>
        </DocsSubSection>
        <DocsSubSection Title="Invalid state" Id="invalid">
            <p>Set <code>Invalid="true"</code> to show the invalid state. The checkbox gets a red border and ring. Add <code>Class="text-destructive"</code> to the label to show error styling.</p>
            <ComponentPreview CodeFiles="@(new[] { Snippets.Components_Checkbox_Examples_CheckboxInvalidExample })">
                <CheckboxInvalidExample />
            </ComponentPreview>
        </DocsSubSection>
    </DocsSection>
</ComponentDocPage>

@code {
    private static readonly ComponentMetadata Metadata = ComponentRegistryService.GetMetadata("Checkbox");

    private const string InstallCommand = "shadcnblazor component add checkbox";
}


